					<li class="tag__item"><i class="fa-solid fa-user-large mr-2"></i> Len Bass</li>
					<li class="tag__item"><i class="fa-solid fa-user-large mr-2"></i> Paul Clements</li>
					<li class="tag__item"><i class="fa-solid fa-book-open"></i> 624</li>
					<li class="tag__item play green">
						<a href="https://www.amazon.com/Software-Architecture-Practice-3rd-Engineering/dp/0321815734" target="_blank"><i class="fa-solid fa-cart-shopping"></i> Comprar</a>
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</article>
		<article class="postcard light yellow">
			<a class="postcard__img_link" href="#">
				<img class="postcard__img" src="https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/61r4tYVsRVL._SY385_.jpg" alt="Clean Architecture" />
			</a>
			<div class="postcard__text t-dark">
				<h1 class="postcard__title yellow"><a href="#">Clean Architecture: A Craftsman's Guide to Software Structure and Design</a></h1>
				<div class="postcard__subtitle small">
					<time datetime="2020-05-25 12:00:00">
						<i class="fas fa-calendar-alt mr-2"></i> Dom, Set 10th 2017
					</time>
				</div>
				<div class="postcard__bar"></div>
				<div class="postcard__preview-txt"> En este libro, Robert C. Martin ("Uncle Bob") expone su visión sobre cómo estructurar sistemas de software de manera que sean robustos, flexibles y fáciles de mantener. El libro abarca conceptos clave de arquitectura y proporciona directrices prácticas para aplicar estos principios en proyectos reales.</div>
				<ul class="postcard__tagbox">
					<li class="tag__item"><i class="fa-solid fa-user-large mr-2"></i> Robert C. Martin</li>
